\b0 \'a0- for example, revealing the identity of supporters or identifying people who were present at a particular event.
\f1\fs24 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\fs20 \uc0\u61623 
\f2 	
\f0 The risk of your\'a0
\b private information being revealed to a third party
\b0 \'a0without your consent.
\f1\fs24 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\fs20 \uc0\u61623 
\f2 	
\f0 The risk that your\'a0
\b account details (username and password) are discovered
\b0 , and that someone may impersonate you.
\f1\fs24 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\fs20 \uc0\u61623 
\f2 	
\f0 The risk of your account being\'a0
\b deleted or suspended
\b0 .
\f1\fs24 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\fs20 \uc0\u61623 
\f2 	
\f0 The risk that\'a0
\b Facebook is blocked or becomes inaccessible
\b0 .
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\sa312

\f0\fs20 \cf0 in general, you should only use Facebook to share information that you consider\'a0
\b public
\b0 . Public information can be freely distributed by you, your organization, and your supporters, without any risk to individuals or organizational operations. In communicating public information, you can send and receive this information without taking any precautions.
